claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: The image shows page 2 of an MMWR document, featuring a table of contents on the left and text on the right outlining ACIP recommendations, CDC publication information, and lists of editorial and production staff. There is no graphical data or study results presented. does not support the claim because the image contains only organizational, publication, and recommendation text without any data comparing antibody responses between higher-dose recombinant and standard-dose egg-based influenza vaccines.
